Hey, what’s up guys so I’m sure most of
you know that Ryzen CPUs can benefit from

increasing RAM speed, even those who use an
Intel CPU.

But the question is, how does that translate
to fps?

Or in other words, how much fps can we get
from buying faster RAM?
Should you just get the fastest one?

Well, I guess it’s best to just go find
out.

Of course, as always you’ll see the specs
of the PC used for this test before the benchmarks.
Enjoy.

So, as you probably guessed, I would recommend
buying RAM no slower than 3000 MHz, preferably
3200 MHz, depending on the prices.

And, of course, just to be clear, this is
only if you’re planning to get a Ryzen CPU

or already have one and are looking to upgrade
your RAM.

Don’t expect this much difference in performance
with Intel CPUs.
